      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64e6bb07e7336.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64e6bb504420c.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64e6bb5569844.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64e6bb59ce371.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64e6bfdb6fd72.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64e6bfea9d628.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Perfection!&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;Overhaul&lt;/em&gt;: Fixed map files so everything is where it should be. Fixed the mod file to not have the entirety of the TOTK mod I made, Mod should be perfect now!&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here is a port of the Champion's Leathers as well as the lowered Hylian Hood variant ported from The Legend of Zelda: Tears of the Kingdom. With its own physics and model, it feels like Link traveled back in time from The Upheaval to the Calamity. Each armor piece has upgrade levels and their respective Defense stats. The Hylian Hood can be purchased for 60 rupees from the Hateno Village armor shop. The Champion's Leathers can be obtained from a chest placed on top of Hyrule castle near a ladder in the main tower. If you find any bugs or things that might be out of place, let me know in the commments.&lt;br&gt;Enjoy!&lt;br&gt;Note: When buying the Hylian Hood, the armor on the manequin will not disappear. This is something that I am trying to figure out. If you know how to fix this, let me know inside the comment section. Thanks!&lt;br&gt;Note: Last Champion's Leathers Upgrade does not take away your Master Sword. The game only checks if you have one. The Weapons in this game do not have a quantity, if anything, it could take 1 off your durability which isn't even one hit.</description>
